block title
  | Configuration

block content
  h1.SG-h1 Configuration

  h2.SG-h2 Configuration file
  p.SG-p.
    By default, Nucleus will look for a config.nucleus.json in the current directory. If none is given, default parameters will be used. Also, command line arguments have a greater priority than configuration values.
  p.SG-p.
    To easily get your style guide set up, use the step-by-step configuration generator:
  code.
    nucleus init

  h2.SG-h2 Available options

  h3.SG-h3 Config file
  p.SG-p The configuration file that shall be used.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label CLI flag
      div.SG-config__value --config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value config.nucleus.json
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Example
      div.SG-config__value nucleus --config styleguide-config.json

  h3.SG-h3 Title
  p.SG-p Lets you overwrite the title of the style guide.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label CLI flag
      div.SG-config__value --title
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value title
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value Nucleus
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Example
      div.SG-config__value nucleus --title StyleBook

  h3.SG-h3 Target
  p.SG-p Target folder to build the style guide to.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label CLI flag
      div.SG-config__value --target
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value target
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value ./styleguide
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Example
      div.SG-config__value nucleus --target ./public/styleguide

  h3.SG-h3 CSS includes
  p.SG-p To preview the components, you need to specify the path (URI) to your CSS file. You may also pass multiple paths as array.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label CLI flag
      div.SG-config__value --css
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value css
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value none
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Example
      div.SG-config__value nucleus --css /assets/app.css

  h3.SG-h3 Template
  p.SG-p If you want customize the generated layout you can copy the [default theme](https://github.com/holidaypirates/nucleus/tree/master/assets/views) and customize it.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label CLI flag
      div.SG-config__value --template
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value template
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value undefined
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Example
      div.SG-config__value nucleus --template=./styleguide/my-theme

  h3.SG-h3 Placeholder Image Service
  p.SG-p Lets you override the default image placeholder service. The value will be used in a template literal, and can accept the width, and height parameters.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label CLI flag
      div.SG-config__value --placeholderservice
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value placeholderService
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value false
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Example
      div.SG-config__value nucleus --placeholderService http://placehold.it/${width}x${height}

  h3.SG-h3 Static dummy texts and images
  p.SG-p For easier visual regression testing, you may disable the generation of randomized lipsum texts and image placeholders. With this option enabled, you will always get the same (boring) placeholders.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label CLI flag
      div.SG-config__value --norandom
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value staticLipsum
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value false
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Example
      div.SG-config__value nucleus --norandom

  h3.SG-h3 Verbose level
  p.SG-p To defines the vebosity level of the console output. For silent output set 0, for debug mode set 3.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label CLI flag
      div.SG-config__value --verbose
      div.SG-config__row
        div.SG-config__label Config key
        div.SG-config__value verbose
        div.SG-config__row
          div.SG-config__label Default value
          div.SG-config__value 3
          div.SG-config__row
            div.SG-config__label Example
            div.SG-config__value nucleus --verbose 2

  h3.SG-h3 Files to crawl
  p.SG-p Path to your scss files that nuceleus use for generating source
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value files
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value ["*.scss", "**/*.scss"]

  h3.SG-h3 Javascript files includes
  p.SG-p To add your javascipt, you need to specify the path (URI) to your Javascript file. You may also pass multiple paths as array.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value scripts
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value null
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Example
      div.SG-config__value ["../js/vendor.js", "../js/app.js"]

  h3.SG-h3 Css namespace
  p.SG-p If you use a CSS namespace class around your style, it will appear on the parent node preview.
  div.SG-config
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Config key
      div.SG-config__value namespace
    div.SG-config__row
      div.SG-config__label Default value
      div.SG-config__value page
